#
# wic image layout for nclawzero cixmini (Cix Sky1 / CP8180 — Minisforum MS-R1).
#
# GPT partitioning, two partitions:
#   1. /boot ESP (FAT, 512 MiB) — UEFI loader + kernel + initrd. Cix's
#      shipping firmware boots via UEFI from this ESP, looking for the
#      EFI_PROVIDER's image (systemd-boot or grub-efi per machine.conf).
#   2. /     rootfs (ext4)     — extra-space sized so first-boot growpart
#      / systemd-resize machinery can fill the destination disk on a wic.gz
#      flashed to a larger NVMe / USB.
#
# No swap partition by design: cixmini is a fleet edge device (64 GB RAM,
# 28 W TDP) with workloads that should not page. Swap can be added at
# runtime via /var/swapfile if a specific use case requires it; baking a
# swap partition into the wic forces every operator to inherit it.
#
# Kernel command-line: the bootloader --append BELOW includes ${APPEND}
# from conf/machine/cixmini.conf, plus the rootfs hints. machine.conf
# APPEND is "console=tty0 console=ttyAMA0,115200 earlycon clk_ignore_unused".
# clk_ignore_unused is REQUIRED on Sky1 until upstream clock handling is
# complete; without it the kernel may panic during clk subsystem init.

part /boot --source bootimg-efi --sourceparams="loader=${EFI_PROVIDER},initrd=${INITRAMFS_IMAGE}-${MACHINE}.${INITRAMFS_FSTYPES}" --label boot --active --align 1024 --use-uuid --fixed-size 512

part / --source rootfs --fstype=ext4 --label root --align 1024 --use-uuid --extra-space 1024

bootloader --ptable gpt --timeout=3 --append="${APPEND} rootwait rootfstype=ext4"
